The Assessment Centre and Tutoring & Learning Centre (TLC) offer resources and tip sheets to help students succeed, including assessment prep materials and tips for taking tests online. Students who require testing are encouraged to book early to secure time slots. For students with disabilities, George Brown's Accessible Learning Services provide academic supports and services. Students must register with the team to receive these services and can attend accessible orientation events. Additionally, there are workshops and videos available to help students navigate college life with disabilities. The contact email for information is [letstalk@georgebrown.ca](mailto:letstalk@georgebrown.ca). The phone number is 416-415-2000, with a TTY number of 1-877-515-5559.
